{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"beaten-tame-cardinal","description":"## Why\nDetector matches are retained only when `location.file` is exactly equal to an entry in\n`changed_files`, with neither side normalized\n(`src/rebar/grounding/.../detectors.py:58,70,74`); the existing test uses exact spellings\n`app.py`/`other.py`. A location and a changed-file entry that denote the same file with\ndifferent spellings (`./app.py`, absolute path, `a//b.py`, symlink, unicode form) silently\ndrop a real high-severity match. VALIDATED.\n\n## What\nEstablish a canonical path contract (normalize both sides here, or document+assert an\nupstream canonicalization guarantee) and add tests for the variant path forms.\n\n## Scope\n- `detectors.py` diff-scope filter; `tests/unit/test_code_review_ws5.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Both sides are normalized (or the upstream canonical-path contract is asserted at\n      this boundary).\n- [ ] Tests cover `./app.py`, an absolute path under repo_root, repeated separators, and a\n      platform-appropriate separator/unicode variant — each still matches its changed file.\n- [ ] A genuinely-different file still does NOT match.\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"e4cf-dfce-4166-4215","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":3,"tags":["p2","security","grounding"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Define and test the security-detector diff-scope path contract"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784830906441001,"uuid":"b9e3296b-f414-4472-9acf-46ecac6c91c9"}